article.headline: Michigan 66, Delaware State 48
article.story: ANN ARBOR, Mich. (AP) -- Courtney Sims scored 14 of his 19 points in the second half to help Michigan pull away from Delaware State for a 66-48 win Wednesday. The victory snapped a two-game losing streak for the Wolverines (7-5). Chris Hunter added 15 points for Michigan. The Wolverines finish their non-conference schedule with a Friday game against N.C.-Asheville before opening Big Ten Conference play next week at Iowa. Delaware State (3-9), playing on the road for the 11th time this season, lost its third consecutive game. Michigan never trailed after taking a 5-4 lead, but the Hornets hung around and pulled to within 46-41 on a 3-pointer by Aaron Williams midway through the second half. The Wolverines then pushed the ball inside and went on an 11-0 run, including eight points from Sims, to take a 57-41 lead. Delaware State was never closer than 12 points the rest of the way. Williams led the Hornets with 18 points, while Jahsha Bluntt had 17.
